text:"SIRUM is making medications affordable for all. We’re a small (~30) but quickly growing team that’s passionate about our mission of reimagining healthcare access for those in need. We come from organizations like McKinsey

We like to solve tough problems and are determined to improve healthcare access for families who have trouble affording the medications they need to stay healthy.

We are currently hiring for our Atlanta Offices as well as some fully remote roles. We have opportunities for staff/principal software developers and product managers who are ex-developers.

If you want to work in healthcare
column2: were going to make a new year's resolution to find mission-driven work
column3: and thrive in a startup environment
column4: then we may be a good fit. If you see a position that you like then apply at https://boards.greenhouse.io/sirum. Even if you don’t see something that’s the right fit right now
column5: email adam -at- sirum.org - we love hearing from folks on hackernews who share our mission."

column1: title:Sirum (YC W15) is hiring developers to help uninsured people afford medicine

column3:
founder of Meticulous.

Our mission is to make the world's code safe
column4:
performant and reliable. We're starting with a tool to catch JavaScript regressions in web applications with zero-effort from developers.

How it works: Insert a single line of JavaScript onto your site
column5:
and we record thousands of real user sessions. We then replay these sessions on new code to automatically catch bugs before they hit production. You can watch a 60-second demo at meticulous.ai.

We are a London-based YC company. Our team previously worked at Dropbox
column6: Opendoor and Google. We just raised $4m
column7: and are backed by some of the best founders and technical leaders in Silicon Valley
column13:
Jared Friedman (YC partner and former CTO of Scribd) and a bunch of other incredible folks.

Catching JavaScript regressions is just the start. There is an entire category of products to build on top of replay. This ranges from automatic UI previews to revealing the performance impact of frontend code.

We want to change the way the world develops software
column14:
and influence software approaches for decades to come.

We are hiring an onsite founding engineer to join our team of two.

You will have autonomy in building out this technology
column15:
but here are a few problems you might work on:

- Build a distributed system to concurrently replay thousands of sessions
column16:
such that a developer gets a result in seconds.

- Speed up the replay of sessions in a way that retains determinism.

- Derive algorithms to detect sessions that cover differing code paths and edge cases
column17:
and ignore sessions that are too similar.

- Help build out a team of world-class
column20: you get to shape the company
column21:
and build the culture and technology from the ground up.

What we look for:

In a sentence: Technically brilliant
column23:
combined with a self-awareness and strong desire to improve.

We're currently only looking to bring on folks with mid-to-senior level skill sets. You should have strong web fundamentals and a deep love for software engineering. Maybe you enjoy programming books like Clean Code
column25: Pragmatic Programmer etc. or enjoy hacking on interesting side projects. You value transparency and candid feedback
column26:
and are driven by a strong desire to become the best engineer you can be.

What you get:

Compensation: We want outrageously talented individuals. This means we offer commensurately outrageous equity grants. The equity grant will be 2% or greater (a 2% grant is $600k at last valuation) with employee-friendly terms (10 year exercise window on options). We pay £100k-£150k in base salary
column27:
along with top of line benefits and perks. You can read about our values here https://sumptuous-lungfish-609.notion.site/Meticulous-values...

Learning: You will be given the space and time to up-level yourself as an engineer in terms of conferences
column29: or whatever you think will be most valuable. We will also set you up with mentorship
column31:
from top engineering leaders (folks running 100-engineer organizations at the world's leading tech companies).

If this sounds interesting
column32: please reach out to me at gabe [at] meticulous [dot] ai with “HN” in the subject line and 2-3 sentences about what you find interesting about Meticulous and your resume/LinkedIn/GitHub."

text:"Hi all! We are looking for frontend and full stack engineers to help us democratize deep learning for manufacturing and industrials. We have an all-star deep learning team and want engineers who can work with us to build out customer facing tools to expose our state of the art algorithms directly to the customer. You will learn a ton about manufacturing and deep learning. The front end work will be very interesting
column2: leveraging real time technologies as well as trying to optimize a massive amount of imaging data. Interested in the challenge? Reach out to me at russell@overview.ai or apply directly https://jobs.lever.co/Overview"
